description:
&lt;p&gt;East &amp; North Hertfordshire NHS Trust have embarked upon a period of significant change to reconfigure acute services as part of a major strategic change within Hertfordshire. We are investing over a £100 million in our hospitals, which will help our staff provide the best care to their patients. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We employ 5,000 staff and can offer a wide variety of opportunities. Our hospitals, Lister Hospital in Stevenage, QEII Hospital in Welwyn Garden City and Hertford County Hospital, are in busy towns with good amenities and leisure activities. London and Cambridge are only 30 minutes away by train.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Applications are invited for an enthusiastic and experienced orthoptists to take on the role of Deputy Head Orthoptist at East and North Herts NHS Trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will be based at the Lister Hospital in Stevenage but the successful candidate may also be required to provide outpatient clinics at the New QE2 Hospital in Welwyn Garden City and Hertford County Hospital in Hertford and also at our community health centers within the county.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Ophthalmology service is currently provided by 6 consultant ophthalmologists, specialising in the areas of Paediatric Ophthalmology, Medical retina, Glaucoma, Oculoplastics and Vitreoretinal surgery. The consultants are supported by a comprehensive team of associate specialists, including junior training posts which are part of the Cambridge deanery. The Allied Health Team is comprised of six orthoptists, six optometrists, ophthalmic nurses and ophthalmic imaging specialists. The Trust is actively supporting the development of extended role working for Allied Health Professionals in line with the Royal College of Ophthalmology’s Common Clinical Competencies Framework; the successful candidate would be instrumental in aiding the development of these roles within the orthoptic service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates must have a BSc or equivalent in Orthoptics and evidence of further post graduate study. Candidates must also have HCPC registration and be able to demonstrate extensive post registration experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A broad knowledge of clinical orthoptic management and excellent communication skills are essential. Previous experience of mentorship or management of junior staff would be advantageous.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;East and North Herts Trust is committed to research and audit; the successful applicant will be expected to participate with new and ongoing audits and research projects as part of their role. Personal development is encouraged, as we are keen for individuals to pursue and develop areas of special interest.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;East and North Herts NHS Trust is exempt from the Rehabilitation of Offenders Act 1974. All positions within the Trust require working regularly or unsupervised with children or vulnerable adults will require an enhanced DBS disclosure. The Trust is committed to safeguarding children and vulnerable adults.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Matthew Price, Head Orthoptist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address : matthewprice@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number : 07778198997&lt;/p&gt;
